The paper deals with the problem of semantic grasping, which is a subfield of robotics that involves selecting stable grasps suitable for specific object manipulation tasks. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses neural networks to learn suitable grasps from data, which falls under cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the importance of balancing memorization and generalization of contexts, which is a topic in cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper presents robot experiments, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
